x4freetext: On tritiated Ti, producing 2.2 x 10**8 neutrons
Ra-226 alpha-particle source was used for detectors
and 5% C-O2 at 20deg C giving a density of 1.28mg/cm2,
forming a counter telescope together with
NE102 of 12.7 microns thickness on an XP 1020.
interaction of reaction products with counter gas -
2 to 10% for singly charged, 5 to 20% for doubly
background, arising to 25% from the counting gas,
to 60% from the tantalum support, to 15% from the
tantalum diaphragm on the solid state detector,
.Angular resolution of solid state detector was 10%,
its energy resolution for 5.3MeV alphas between 1.6
global time resolution of the counting system 0.69
efficiency of the telescope better than 99% for
statistical error in Monte Carlo calculation of
systematical error due to uncertainty in lateral
systematical error due to uncertainty in axial sample
